    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mt-16 md:mt-20 w-full lg:max-w-[780px] rounded-xl shadow-md border border-gray-100 bg-white mx-auto">
    <div class="p-6 border-b border-gray-200 rounded-tl-xl rounded-tr-xl">
      <h2 class="font-semibold tracking-tight text-[21px] mb-6">Weekly SEV Drills</h2>
      <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        GPT emails you an incident <span class="font-semibold">every Monday</span>, and asks you to reason your way out of it.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-6">
        <span class="font-semibold">Text-based puzzles</span>, with open-ended questions that surface <span class="font-semibold">core infra blind spots</span> every week.
      </p>

      <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
        5 engineers, 500 engineers, doesn't matter. They all start with the same SEV, but scramble to fix it in <span class="font-semibold">private email threads</span>. The more they explain their thoughts, the more GPT can course correct.
      </p>

      <p class="leading-relaxed">
        Admins get <span class="font-semibold">anonymous monthly report emails</span>. Risky team-wide trends, not specific names.
